President Obama sends warm wishes to those celebrating the Hmong New Year. He acknowledges the struggles and sacrifices made by the Hmong community, who have come to the United States as refugees escaping persecution. The President recognizes the contributions the Hmong community has made to America and highlights the importance of their culture. The Hmong New Year is a time for celebration, featuring food, colorful clothes, music, and games. President Obama wishes those celebrating a prosperous and healthy New Year in the Hmong language, Nyob zoo xyoo tshiab.